      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Small field but most have a decent chance. DOLCE VITA (6) was lining up for only the third time when a game winner over this distance at Wyong last start. Contested the lead that day then dug deep to cling on in quick time. Nicely drawn and can progress to this level. ALL THE WAY MAE (7) tried hard but found a couple better when fresh from a spell over this distance at Hawkesbury last time out. Didn't come up last prep but that recent return was positive. Can go on with the job now. GRAVEL ROAD (3) has not raced since starting at $2.05 and winning on debut by the barest margin over 1100m at Wyong on 10 February. Trialled well recently and looks set to make an immediate impact. LUSKINTYRE (5) is back after a seven-month spell. Found form at the end of the maiden campaign when the tracks dried out. This looks a nice race to launch the second campaign. WAVETON (8) dominated at Tamworth last time and while this is much harder she is progressing in impressive style.",
